## Repository layout

- `main.nf` — workflow entry point
- `nextflow.config` — top-level configuration and selected execution profile
- `conf/` — base, modules, and executor-specific config
- `assets/` — sample metadata and tiny example inputs
- `workflows/`, `modules/`, `subworkflows/` — extension points for pipeline logic
- `docs/` — development and execution notes

## Output policy

- `{{ outdir }}/` is for lightweight report-style outputs you may choose to commit.
- `data/` is ignored by Git and intended for large inputs or bulky derived files.
- `work/` and Nextflow runtime directories are ignored.

## Git bootstrap

After `pixi install`, commit the generated scaffold together with `pixi.lock` and `{{ _copier_conf.answers_file }}`.

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit from Copier template"
```

## Updating from the template

Keep `{{ _copier_conf.answers_file }}` committed if you want to support `copier update` later.
